  corruption: silicon is clean for BRAM-resident single-master
  workload → the bug is **upload-path-related** or **kernel
  workload-pattern-related**, not a generic data-path
  failure.
- [ ] Add a hwsim variant (Verilator-driven) of this same
  firmware → confirms RTL is also clean (expected) and gives us
  a sim baseline to compare future regressions against.
- [ ] Probe the JTAG-Avalon-Master upload path with a host-side
  written-vs-readback verify covering the upper 2 MB explicitly.
- [ ] Re-test with a kernel-style workload: BRAM fetch interleaved
  with high-SDRAM data accesses (closer to what Linux actually
  does at boot) to see if concurrent fetch+data access on the
  runtime bus reproduces the corruption.
